{"title_page": "Hidden History of the Human Race", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n|name = Hidden History of the Human Race\n|artist = [[Blood Incantation]]\n|type = studio\n|genre = [[Progressive death metal]]<ref name = \"Pressrelease\"/><ref name = \"EchoesandDust\">{{cite web|author=Owen|date=December 3, 2019|url=https://www.echoesanddust.com/2019/12/blood-incantation-hidden-history-of-the-human-race/|title=Blood Incantation \u2013 Hidden History of the Human Race|website=Echoes and Dust|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n|recorded = June 2019\n|released = November 22, 2019\n|studio = {{plainlist|\n*World Famous Studios\n*(Denver, Colorado)\n}}\n|length = 36:20\n|label = \n|prev_title = Live Vitrification\n|prev_year = 2018\n}}\n'''''Hidden History of the Human Race''''' is the second [[studio album]] of [[Denver, Colorado|Denver]]-based [[death metal]] group [[Blood Incantation]].\n== Production and content ==\nWith ''Hidden History of the Human Race'', Blood Incantation went out to produce \"a genuine and distinctive album of monumental and epic psychedelic/brutal/progressive/technical/ambient/funeral death metal like no other,\" summarized Paul Riedl.<ref name = \"Decibel\">{{cite web|last=Pearce|first=Dutch|date=July 10, 2019|url=https://www.decibelmagazine.com/2019/07/10/studio-report-blood-incantation-the-hidden-history-of-the-human-race/|title=Studio Report: Blood Incantation \u2013 \u201cHidden History of the Human Race\u201d|work=[[Decibel (magazine)|Decibel]]|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref> In comparison to the band's previous studio effort ''Starspawn'' (2016), ''Hidden History of the Human Race''{{'}} mixing is more upfront and harsh, with an increase in meaty guitars, clear drums, and reverb and delay effects.<ref name = \"Decibel\"/> The track listing is set up in the tradition of 1970s' [[progressive rock]] albums, with three tracks on side A and one long epic on side B.<ref name = \"Decibel\"/> ''Hidden History of the Human Race'' questions traditional and agreed-upon theories about the human species, specifically evolution, consciousness, and how they have historically developed societies.<ref name = \"Pressrelease\"/><ref name = \"WestWord\">{{cite web|last=Childers|first=Oakland|date=January 8, 2020|url=https://www.westword.com/music/blood-incantation-on-hidden-history-of-the-human-race-11597317|title=Blood Incantation on ''Hidden History of the Human Race''|work=[[Westword]]|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref> \n\nNot counting \"The Giza Power Plant\" written in 2013,<ref name = \"Decibel\"/> writing of ''Hidden History of the Human Race'' lasted for more than the years; With the intention of making challenging metal music, members of Blood Incantation intentionally wrote parts they couldn't perform initially, and rehearsed them for more than a month before recording began.<ref name = \"WestWord\"/> ''Hidden History of the Human Race'' was analog-recorded at World Famous Studios in Denver starting June 21, 2019.<ref name = \"Pressrelease\">{{cite web|url=http://www.darkdescentrecords.com/store/index.php?main_page=product_info&products_id=11443|title=Blood Incantation \u2013 Hidden History of the Human Race CD|website=Dark Descent|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref><ref name = \"Decibel\"/> The artwork for ''Hidden History of the Human Race'' uses the front cover of [[Brian Aldiss]]' novel ''Space, Time and Nathaniel'' (1957)<ref name = \"EchoesandDust\"/> created by British painter [[Bruce Pennington]],<ref name = \"Pressrelease\"/> which the band chose to use before they recorded their debut LP.<ref name = \"Decibel\"/>\n\n== Release ==\nAlthough originally planned to be released in coincidence with Blood Incantation's 2019 North American tour with [[Immolation (band)|Immolation]], ''Hidden History of the Human Race'' was pushed back to a later fall 2019 date due to the deadline being too limited.<ref name = \"Decibel\"/> \n== Critical response ==\n{{Album ratings\n|ADM = 8.6/10<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.anydecentmusic.com/review/10178/Blood-Incantation-Hidden-History-of-the-Human-Race.aspx|title=Hidden History of the Human Race by Blood Incantation|website=[[AnyDecentMusic]]|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n|MC = 91/100<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/music/hidden-history-of-the-human-race/blood-incantation|title=Hidden History of the Human Race by Blood Incantation|website=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n|rev1 = ''[[Brave Words & Bloody Knuckles]]''\n|rev1Score = 8.5/10<ref name = \"BraveWords\">{{cite web|last=Pratt|first=Greg|date=December 29, 2014|url=http://bravewords.com/reviews/blood-incantation-hidden-history-of-the-human-race|title=Blood Incantation \u2013 Hidden History Of The Human Race|work=[[Brave Words & Bloody Knuckles]]|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n|rev2 = ''[[Exclaim!]]''\n|rev2Score = 9/10<ref name = \"Exclaim\">{{cite web|last=Kelleher|first=Jack|date=November 22, 2019|url=http://exclaim.ca/music/article/blood_incantation-hidden_history_of_the_human_race|title=Blood Incantation Hidden History of the Human Race|work=[[Exclaim!]]|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n|rev4 = ''[[Kerrang!]]''\n|rev4Score = 4/5<ref name = \"Kerrang\">{{cite web|last=Davey|first=Angela|date=November 23, 2019|url=https://www.kerrang.com/reviews/album-review-blood-incantation-hidden-history-of-the-human-race/|title=Album Review: Blood Incantation \u2013 Hidden History of the Human Race|work=[[Kerrang!]]|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n|rev5 = ''[[The Line of Best Fit]]''\n|rev5Score = 10/10<ref name = \"TLOBF\">{{cite web|last=Horton|first=Ross|date=November 27, 2019|url=https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/reviews/albums/blood-incantation-hidden-history-of-the-human-race-album-review|title=Blood Incantation have made the heaviest Christmas present you\u2019ll give this year|work=[[The Line of Best Fit]]|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n|rev6 = ''Metal Injection''\n|rev6Score = 10/10<ref name = \"MetalInjection\">{{cite web|last=Luedtke|first=Christopher|date=December 2, 2019|url=https://metalinjection.net/reviews/blood-incantation-hidden-history-of-the-human-race|title=Blood Incantation ''Hidden History Of The Human Race''|work=Metal Injection|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n|rev7 = ''[[Metal Sucks]]''\n|rev7Score = {{rating|5|5}}<ref name = \"MetalSucks\">{{cite web|last=Treppel|first=Jeff|date=November 18, 2019|url=https://www.metalsucks.net/2019/11/18/album-review-blood-incantation-reveal-the-hidden-history-of-the-human-race/|title=Album Review: Blood Incantation Reveal the ''Hidden History of the Human Race''|work=[[Metal Sucks]]|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n|rev8 = ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''\n|rev8Score = 8.3/10<ref name = \"Pitchfork\">{{cite web|last=Greene|first=Jayson|date=November 27, 2019|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/blood-incantation-hidden-history-of-the-human-race/|title=Blood Incantation: Hidden History of the Human Race|work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n|rev9 = ''[[Sputnikmusic]]''\n|rev9Score = 5/5<ref name = \"Sputnikmusic\">{{cite web|author=Xenophanes|date=November 9, 2019|url=https://www.sputnikmusic.com/review/80497/Blood-Incantation-Hidden-History-of-the-Human-Race/|title=Review: Blood Incantation \u2013 Hidden History of the Human Race|website=[[Sputnikmusic]]|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n|rev10 = ''Toilet Ov Hell''\n|rev10Score = {{rating|5|5}}<ref name = \"Toilet\">{{cite web|last=Bearikson|first=Leif|date=November 18, 2019|url=https://toiletovhell.com/review-blood-incantation-hidden-history-of-the-human-race/|title=Review: Blood Incantation \u2013 Hidden History of the Human Race|work=Toilet Ov Hell|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\nMost critics called ''Hidden History of the Human Race'' the best metal album of the year.<ref name = \"EchoesandDust\"/>\n== Year-end lists ==\n{|class=\"sortable plainrowheaders wikitable\"\n|-\n! Publication\n! Rank\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| ''[[BrooklynVegan]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.brooklynvegan.com/brooklynvegans-top-50-albums-of-2019/|title=BrooklynVegan\u2019s Top 50 Albums of 2019|work=[[BrooklynVegan]]|date=December 23, 2019|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n| align=center | 47\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| ''[[Decibel (magazine)|Decibel]]''<ref>{{cite web|last=Mudrian|first=Albert|date=November 12, 2019|url=https://www.decibelmagazine.com/2019/11/12/spoiler-here-are-decibels-top-40-albums-of-2019/|title=SPOILER: Here Are Decibel\u2019s Top 40 Albums of 2019|work=Decibel|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n| align=center | 1\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Metal Hammer]]''<ref>{{cite web|last=Munro|first=Scott|date=December 10, 2019|url=https://www.loudersound.com/news/tools-fear-inoculum-named-metal-hammers-album-of-the-year|title=Tool\u2019s Fear Inoculum named Metal Hammer\u2019s album of the year|work=[[Metal Hammer]]|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n| align=center | 24\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/features/lists-and-guides/best-albums-2019/|title=The 50 Best Albums of 2019|date=December 10, 2019|work=Pitchfork|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n| align=center | 41\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]'' (Metal)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/features/lists-and-guides/best-metal-albums-2019/|title=The Best Metal Albums of 2019|date=December 18, 2019|work=Pitchfork|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n| align=center | Unranked\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[The Quietus]]''<ref>{{cite web|last=Doran|first=John|date=December 18, 2019|url=https://thequietus.com/articles/27504-quietus-albums-of-the-year-2019-norman-records|title=Quietus Albums Of The Year 2019 (In Association With Norman Records)|work=[[The Quietus]]|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n| align=center | 58\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Revolver (magazine)|Revolver]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.revolvermag.com/music/25-best-albums-2019|title=25 Best Albums of 2019|work=[[Revolver (magazine)|Revolver]]|date=November 25, 2019|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n| align=center | 25\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Stereogum]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stereogum.com/featured/best-albums-2019/|title=The 50 Best Albums Of 2019|date=December 3, 2019|work=[[Stereogum]]|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n| align=center | 44\n|}\n==Track listing==\nSource: <ref name = \"Pressrelease\"/>\n{{Track listing\n| title1 = Slave Species of the Gods \n| length1 = 5:31\n| title2 = The Giza Power Plant \n| length2 = 7:06\n| title3 = Inner Paths (to Outer Space) \n| length3 = 5:38\n| title4 = Awakening From the Dream of Existence to the Multidimensional Nature of Our Reality (Mirror of the Soul) \n| length4 = 18:05\n}}\n== Charts ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2019)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{albumchart|UKRock|34|date=20191206|accessdate=April 22, 2020|rowheader=true}}\n|- \n! scope=\"row\"|US Top Current Albums (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/blood-incantation/chart-history/TCL/song/1168129|title=Blood Incantation Chart History (Top Current Album Sales)|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n| 36\n|-\n{{albumchart|BillboardHeatseekers|1|artist=Blood Incantation|accessdate=April 22, 2020|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n{{albumchart|BillboardIndependent|6|artist=Blood Incantation|accessdate=April 22, 2020|rowheader=true}}\n|}\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n[[Category:2019 albums]]\n[[Category:Death metal albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n|name = Hidden History of the Human Race\n|artist = [[Blood Incantation]]\n|type = studio\n|genre = [[Progressive death metal]]<ref name = \"Pressrelease\"/><ref name = \"EchoesandDust\">{{cite web|author=Owen|date=December 3, 2019|url=https://www.echoesanddust.com/2019/12/blood-incantation-hidden-history-of-the-human-race/|title=Blood Incantation \u2013 Hidden History of the Human Race|website=Echoes and Dust|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n|recorded = June 2019\n|released = November 22, 2019\n|studio = {{plainlist|\n*World Famous Studios\n*(Denver, Colorado)\n}}\n|length = 36:20\n|label = \n|prev_title = Live Vitrification\n|prev_year = 2018\n}}\n'''''Hidden History of the Human Race''''' is the second [[studio album]] of [[Denver, Colorado|Denver]]-based [[death metal]] group [[Blood Incantation]].\n== Production and content ==\nWith ''Hidden History of the Human Race'', Blood Incantation went out to produce \"a genuine and distinctive album of monumental and epic psychedelic/brutal/progressive/technical/ambient/funeral death metal like no other,\" summarized Paul Riedl.<ref name = \"Decibel\">{{cite web|last=Pearce|first=Dutch|date=July 10, 2019|url=https://www.decibelmagazine.com/2019/07/10/studio-report-blood-incantation-the-hidden-history-of-the-human-race/|title=Studio Report: Blood Incantation \u2013 \u201cHidden History of the Human Race\u201d|work=[[Decibel (magazine)|Decibel]]|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref> In comparison to the band's previous studio effort ''Starspawn'' (2016), ''Hidden History of the Human Race''{{'}} mixing is more upfront and harsh, with an increase in meaty guitars, clear drums, and reverb and delay effects.<ref name = \"Decibel\"/> The track listing is set up in the tradition of 1970s' [[progressive rock]] albums, with three tracks on side A and one long epic on side B.<ref name = \"Decibel\"/> ''Hidden History of the Human Race'' questions traditional and agreed-upon theories about the human species, specifically evolution, consciousness, and how they have historically developed societies.<ref name = \"Pressrelease\"/><ref name = \"WestWord\">{{cite web|last=Childers|title=Oakland|date=January 8, 2020|url=https://www.westword.com/music/blood-incantation-on-hidden-history-of-the-human-race-11597317|title=Blood Incantation on ''Hidden History of the Human Race''|work=[[Westword]]|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref> \n\nNot counting \"The Giza Power Plant\" written in 2013,<ref name = \"Decibel\"/> writing of ''Hidden History of the Human Race'' lasted for more than the years; With the intention of making challenging metal music, members of Blood Incantation intentionally wrote parts they couldn't perform initially, and rehearsed them for more than a month before recording began.<ref name = \"WestWord\"/> ''Hidden History of the Human Race'' was analog-recorded at World Famous Studios in Denver starting June 21, 2019.<ref name = \"Pressrelease\">{{cite web|url=http://www.darkdescentrecords.com/store/index.php?main_page=product_info&products_id=11443|title=Blood Incantation \u2013 Hidden History of the Human Race CD|website=Dark Descent|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref><ref name = \"Decibel\"/> The artwork for ''Hidden History of the Human Race'' uses the front cover of [[Brian Aldiss]]' novel ''Space, Time and Nathaniel'' (1957)<ref name = \"EchoesandDust\"/> created by British painter [[Bruce Pennington]],<ref name = \"Pressrelease\"/> which the band chose to use before they recorded their debut LP.<ref name = \"Decibel\"/>\n\n== Release ==\nAlthough originally planned to be released in coincidence with Blood Incantation's 2019 North American tour with [[Immolation (band)|Immolation]], ''Hidden History of the Human Race'' was pushed back to a later fall 2019 date due to the deadline being too limited.<ref name = \"Decibel\"/> \n== Critical response ==\n{{Album ratings\n|ADM = 8.6/10<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.anydecentmusic.com/review/10178/Blood-Incantation-Hidden-History-of-the-Human-Race.aspx|title=Hidden History of the Human Race by Blood Incantation|website=[[AnyDecentMusic]]|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n|MC = 91/100<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/music/hidden-history-of-the-human-race/blood-incantation|title=Hidden History of the Human Race by Blood Incantation|website=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n|rev1 = ''[[Brave Words & Bloody Knuckles]]''\n|rev1Score = 8.5/10<ref name = \"BraveWords\">{{cite web|last=Pratt|first=Greg|date=December 29, 2014|url=http://bravewords.com/reviews/blood-incantation-hidden-history-of-the-human-race|title=Blood Incantation \u2013 Hidden History Of The Human Race|work=[[Brave Words & Bloody Knuckles]]|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n|rev2 = ''[[Exclaim!]]''\n|rev2Score = 9/10<ref name = \"Exclaim\">{{cite web|last=Kelleher|first=Jack|date=November 22, 2019|url=http://exclaim.ca/music/article/blood_incantation-hidden_history_of_the_human_race|title=Blood Incantation Hidden History of the Human Race|work=[[Exclaim!]]|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n|rev4 = ''[[Kerrang!]]''\n|rev4Score = 4/5<ref name = \"Kerrang\">{{cite web|last=Davey|first=Angela|date=November 23, 2019|url=https://www.kerrang.com/reviews/album-review-blood-incantation-hidden-history-of-the-human-race/|title=Album Review: Blood Incantation \u2013 Hidden History of the Human Race|work=[[Kerrang!]]|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n|rev5 = ''[[The Line of Best Fit]]''\n|rev5Score = 10/10<ref name = \"TLOBF\">{{cite web|last=Horton|first=Ross|date=November 27, 2019|url=https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/reviews/albums/blood-incantation-hidden-history-of-the-human-race-album-review|title=Blood Incantation have made the heaviest Christmas present you\u2019ll give this year|work=[[The Line of Best Fit]]|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n|rev6 = ''Metal Injection''\n|rev6Score = 10/10<ref name = \"MetalInjection\">{{cite web|last=Luedtke|first=Christopher|date=December 2, 2019|url=https://metalinjection.net/reviews/blood-incantation-hidden-history-of-the-human-race|title=Blood Incantation ''Hidden History Of The Human Race''|work=Metal Injection|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n|rev7 = ''[[Metal Sucks]]''\n|rev7Score = {{rating|5|5}}<ref name = \"MetalSucks\">{{cite web|last=Treppel|first=Jeff|date=November 18, 2019|url=https://www.metalsucks.net/2019/11/18/album-review-blood-incantation-reveal-the-hidden-history-of-the-human-race/|title=Album Review: Blood Incantation Reveal the ''Hidden History of the Human Race''|work=[[Metal Sucks]]|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n|rev8 = ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''\n|rev8Score = 8.3/10<ref name = \"Pitchfork\">{{cite web|last=Greene|first=Jayson|date=November 27, 2019|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/blood-incantation-hidden-history-of-the-human-race/|title=Blood Incantation: Hidden History of the Human Race|work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n|rev9 = ''[[Sputnikmusic]]''\n|rev9Score = 5/5<ref name = \"Sputnikmusic\">{{cite web|author=Xenophanes|date=November 9, 2019|url=https://www.sputnikmusic.com/review/80497/Blood-Incantation-Hidden-History-of-the-Human-Race/|title=Review: Blood Incantation \u2013 Hidden History of the Human Race|website=[[Sputnikmusic]]|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n|rev10 = ''Toilet Ov Hell''\n|rev10Score = {{rating|5|5}}<ref name = \"Toilet\">{{cite web|last=Bearikson|first=Leif|date=November 18, 2019|url=https://toiletovhell.com/review-blood-incantation-hidden-history-of-the-human-race/|title=Review: Blood Incantation \u2013 Hidden History of the Human Race|work=Toilet Ov Hell|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\nMost critics called ''Hidden History of the Human Race'' the best metal album of the year.<ref name = \"EchoesandDust\"/>\n== Year-end lists ==\n{|class=\"sortable plainrowheaders wikitable\"\n|-\n! Publication\n! Rank\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| ''[[BrooklynVegan]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.brooklynvegan.com/brooklynvegans-top-50-albums-of-2019/|title=BrooklynVegan\u2019s Top 50 Albums of 2019|work=[[BrooklynVegan]]|date=December 23, 2019|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n| align=center | 47\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| ''[[Decibel (magazine)|Decibel]]''<ref>{{cite web|last=Mudrian|first=Albert|date=November 12, 2019|url=https://www.decibelmagazine.com/2019/11/12/sp