ona (1941) |publisher=Wrecksite |accessdate=18 October 2011}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Fokion||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk off [[Psara]] by Luftwaffe aircraft. Two crew were killed.<ref name=NH044122/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.historisches-marinearchiv.de/projekte/verluste_griechenland/ausgabe.php?rubrik=%&where_value=451 |title=Fokion |publisher=www.historisches-marinearchiv.de |accessdate=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{MV|Franco Martelli||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Kingdom of Italy|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the Mediterranean Sea ({{coord|46|31|N|8|46|E}}) by {{HMS|Urge}} ({{navy|UK}}).<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Moscha L Goulandris||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and damaged off [[Chalkis]] by Luftwaffe aircraft and was beached. After further bombing on 20 and 23 April she was declared a total loss.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=Panduah \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The steel flat sank under tow ({{coord|19|15|N|86|53|E}}).<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German trawler|V-709 Guido M\u00f6hring||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The ''[[vorpostenboot]]'' was torpedoed and sunk in the Bay of Biscay near Port Ley.<ref name=NH044122/><ref name=V709>{{cite web |url=http://www.wrecksite.eu/wreck.aspx?16511 |title=V-709 (Guido M\u00f6hring) (+1941) |publisher=Wrecksite |accessdate=27 December 2011}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Leon||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk off [[Psara]] by Luftwaffe aircraft.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{HMT|Young Ernie}} \n|flag={{navy|UK}}\n|desc=The naval trawler collided with another vessel in the [[River Tyne|Tyne]] 