44122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Maiotis|1888|2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk in the [[Aegean Sea]] by Luftwaffe aircraft. She was later raised, and scrapped in [[Venice]], Italy, in 1949.<ref name=NH044122/><ref>{{csr|register=MSI|id=1092237|shipname=Maiotis |accessdate=6 December 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Maria Stathatou||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk at [[Myloi, Argolis|Myloi]] by Luftwaffe aircraft.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Mountpark||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk in the Atlantic Ocean ({{coord|56|17|N|12|21|W}}) by [[Focke-Wulf Fw 200]] aircraft of I ''Staffeln'', [[Kampfgeschwader 40]], Luftwaffe with the loss of six crew.<ref name=seekrieg194104/><ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Murdoch||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=The cargo ship sprang a leak and sank in the [[North Sea]] off [[Great Yarmouth]], [[Norfolk]].<ref name=Murdoch>{{cite web |url=http://www.wrecksite.eu/wreck.aspx?70288 |title=SS Murdoch (+1941) |publisher=Wrecksite |accessdate=23 December 2011}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Zakynthos||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk off [[Monemvasia]] by Luftwaffe aircraft.<ref name=NH044122/> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==27 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=27 April 1941 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Astir||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk at [[Kapsali]]on by Luftwaffe aircraft.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{MV|Beacon Grange||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the Atlantic Ocean ({{coord|62|05|N|16|20|W}}) by {{GS|U-552||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Ger