at.net |accessdate=23 April 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Nicolaos Nomicos||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The coaster was bombed and sunk at Trisonia-Spilia, Patras by Luftwaffe aircraft. She was later refloated by the Germans and towed to [[Piraeus]], where she was scrapped.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Nicolaou Georgios||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk at [[Nauplia]] by Luftwaffe aircraft.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship= {{ship|Greek auxiliary minelayer|Paralos||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Greece|royalnavy}}\n|desc=World War II: The auxiliary minelayer was sunk at [[Vouliagmeni]] by Luftwaffe aircraft. Salvaged and put in German service as UJ-2103.<ref name=\"Captured Greek submarine chasers\"/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship= {{ship|Greek auxiliary minelayer|Pleias||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The auxiliary survey ship/minelayer was sunk off Missolounghi by Luftwaffe aircraft.<ref>{{csr|register=MSI|id=6108818|shipname=Pleias |accessdate=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Policos||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=([[File: Red_Cross.png|40px]][[International Committee of the Red Cross|Red Cross]]): World War II: The hospital ship was bombed and sunk at [[Methana]] by Luftwaffe aircraft.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Ponta Verde||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Brazil|1889}}\n|desc=The tanker ran aground in the [[Strait of Magellan]] and was wrecked.<ref name=PV>{{cite web |url=http://www.wrecksite.eu/wreck.aspx?152907 |title=SS Ponta Verde (+1941) |publisher=Wrecksite |accessdate=23 December 2011}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{MV|Santa Clara Valley||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk in [[Nauplia]] Bay by Luftwaffe aircraft with the loss of seven lives.<ref name=NH044122/>\n}}\n{{shipwrec